1
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:29,940
[Legend of Zang Hai]

2
00:01:30,060 --> 00:01:32,820
[Episode 17]

3
00:01:34,230 --> 00:01:35,930
Everyone experiences pain and confusion.

4
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,740
Knowing is easy, and doing is hard.

5
00:01:37,790 --> 00:01:39,050
Even the Marquis of Pingjin is no exception.

6
00:01:40,230 --> 00:01:42,380
If you want him to rely on you,

7
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,900
then help ease his burdens.

8
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,290
So, what haunts the Marquis?

9
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,410
It's tied to someone

10
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:53,330
who has long vanished from the Zhuang family.

11
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:57,290
Shen Wan was the daughter of Zhuang Luyin's father's old comrade.

12
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,770
She and Zhuang Luyin grew up together.

13
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:02,330
But to revive the Zhuang name,

14
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:04,260
he gave up on Shen Wan

15
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:07,380
and married Jiang Xiang, daughter of Minister Jiang Jin.

16
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,730
From then on, his career soared.

17
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,730
In the 35th year of Wuhe,

18
00:02:19,190 --> 00:02:20,850
he suffered a major defeat in Dongxia.

19
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,290
The Emperor ordered him to guard the border.

20
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,100
Jiang Xiang refused the hardship

21
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:28,100
and stayed in the Capital with Zhuang Zhifu.

22
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:45,780
Stop!

23
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,010
Life at the border was tough,

24
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,500
yet someone appeared

25
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,690
in his desolate life.

26
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:07,730
That was Shen Wan.

27
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,290
She never married.

28
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:16,100
She came to the border to care for her wounded father.

29
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:18,500
There, she reunited with Zhuang Luyin.

30
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,290
They stayed together at the frontier,

31
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,660
and had a son, Zhuang Zhixing.

32
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,660
When Zhuang Zhixing was five,

33
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:35,010
the court decided to wage war on Dongxia again.

34
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,820
Zhuang Luyin was named the vanguard.

35
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,940
This time, he crushed Dongxia and redeemed his past defeat.

36
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,220
But just as his fame soared

37
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,980
and he earned unparalleled glory,

38
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,610
an unexpected visitor arrived at the border.

39
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:52,410
Jiang Xiang came with Zhuang Zhifu.

40
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,220
She wanted to rekindle their marriage.

41
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,570
Zhuang Luyin was torn.

42
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,980
He dreamed of surpassing his father's legacy.

43
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,060
But slighting Jiang Xiang

44
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:05,500
would offend her father,

45
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,130
a man of immense power.

46
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,940
Yet how could he betray Shen Wan again?

47
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,660
While he wavered,

48
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:15,660
Shen Wan stepped forward.

49
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:18,370
She willingly gave up her place

50
00:04:18,390 --> 00:04:19,460
to make way for Jiang Xiang.

51
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,540
And Zhuang Luyin didn't refuse.

52
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:27,490
After that, he got everything he wanted: title and command.

53
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:30,610
He became a powerful figure in court.

54
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:33,290
Three!

55
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:37,290
He thought he could treat them equally,

56
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,410
and let Shen Wan suffer nothing.

57
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:43,050
But he underestimated Jiang Xiang's ambition and cunning.

58
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:47,540
Since you hold high office,

59
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,370
you should focus on your career.

60
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:50,980
Leave household matters

61
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:53,730
to Jiang Xiang.

62
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,250
Jiang Xiang drove a wedge

63
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,700
between him and Shen Wan,

64
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:20,700
until at last,

65
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,850
Zhuang Luyin believed Shen Wan was unfaithful.

66
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,980
With his silent consent,

67
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:26,700
Jiang Xiang poisoned her.

68
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,220
Mother!

69
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,290
Mother!

70
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,540
Mother!

71
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,580
Don't leave me!

72
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,100
Please!

73
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:47,140
I'm begging you!

74
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:49,250
Mother!

75
00:05:49,430 --> 00:05:50,930
Mother!

76
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,250
Mother!

77
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,340
A great debt is like a deep grudge.

78
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:02,020
No one wants to carry it for life.

79
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:04,900
A debt that can't be repaid over time

80
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,340
turns either into indifference,

81
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,730
or resentment.

82
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:13,730
The selfish usually live the happiest

83
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:14,900
in this world.

84
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:16,700
Why can't he let go

85
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,050
of this one thing?

86
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,930
Is he hung up on Shen Wan of the past,

87
00:06:22,870 --> 00:06:26,020
or ashamed of the man he once was?

88
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,580
No one can say for sure.

89
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,660
And so he refuses

90
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,220
to give even a shred of fatherly love to Zhuang Zhixing.

91
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,340
Because every time he sees him,

92
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,700
he's reminded of the disgrace he used to be.

93
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,540
The more you bury pain like that,

94
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,610
the deeper it takes root.

95
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,370
What kind of strong man wants to admit

96
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,580
to such a weakness inside?

97
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:11,780
My Lord,

98
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:12,790
you were looking for me?

99
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:16,460
Do you know why I asked you to come here?

100
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,460
I believe this place

101
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,780
is where the second young master lived as a child.

102
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:25,460
My Lord summoned me here

103
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,100
because of what I said earlier

104
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,780
about the second young master?

105
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,780
Zhixing

106
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:35,980
was once dearly loved

107
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,340
by me.

108
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:42,170
But over time, we grew distant.

109
00:07:42,830 --> 00:07:44,850
And I've treated him far worse than Zhifu

110
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,370
in recent years.

111
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,580
He's become the disappointing son.

112
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,540
Could it be

113
00:07:52,310 --> 00:07:53,250
that I am also to blame?

114
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:56,810
You are the head of the family.

115
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:59,610
How could you be at fault?

116
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,900
I was just thinking,

117
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:05,220
the garden is full of blooming peonies,

118
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:08,290
so why did you come here alone?

119
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:20,290
I once knew a poor gardener.

120
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,900
He made a living growing plum blossoms.

121
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,250
But they were cheap,

122
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,490
and over time,

123
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:29,410
he became poorer and poorer,

124
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:31,930
barely able to support himself.

125
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:35,850
Then he realized people adored peonies.

126
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,220
They sold for far more.

127
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:40,940
So he switched to growing peonies,

128
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,980
and finally lived a life of comfort.

129
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:44,820
But he told me

130
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:46,370
that deep down,

131
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,850
he still loved

132
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,180
the plum blossoms more.

133
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,420
But it was too late.

134
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,820
The plums in his garden,

135
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,300
left untended,

136
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:58,460
all withered away.

137
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:03,940
That he chose plums when he was poor

138
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,610
shows how deeply he loved them.

139
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,700
But since he sold flowers for a living,

140
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:09,530
he had no choice but to grow peonies.

141
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,490
His beloved plums

142
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,890
faded and died.

143
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,820
Perhaps he blamed himself for that.

144
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,580
But I don't think he was wrong.

145
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:21,980
Why not?

146
00:09:24,150 --> 00:09:25,730
Plum blossoms bloom in winter.

147
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,580
They endure snow and frost, never chasing spring.

148
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:32,130
It's not that the gardener heartlessly chose peonies.

149
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:36,250
It's that the plum chose to bloom in hardship,

150
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,250
and fall into the mud.

151
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:41,180
Had he not turned to peonies,

152
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,060
the whole garden

153
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:44,700
might not have survived the winter.

154
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:48,770
It reminds me of a poem:

155
00:09:50,030 --> 00:09:52,420
"Petals fall dry, already heartbreaking.

156
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,650
How cruel, the storm that follows.

157
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,730
How can such grief be soothed?

158
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,940
Hope lies in fresh buds on new branches."

159
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:06,250
The poet mourned the blossoms lost in the storm,

160
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:08,730
but didn't dwell in sorrow.

161
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,730
Because he believed,

162
00:10:11,790 --> 00:10:13,700
as long as new branches grow,

163
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,890
the plums will bloom again.

164
00:10:18,910 --> 00:10:21,300
The gardener mourned what he lost,

165
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:25,730
unaware a single young plum still lingered in a quiet corner.

166
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,850
It may go unnoticed in the warmth of spring,

167
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,700
but if nurtured with care,

168
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,340
one day, in snow and frost again,

169
00:10:33,910 --> 00:10:37,730
it might stand proud and bloom anew.

170
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,850
What did he say to my father earlier?

171
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,010
My father actually asked about my studies.

172
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,650
That means the Marquis intends to groom you.

173
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,980
His care for you now may even surpass

174
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,890
what he gives to Zhuang Zhifu.

175
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,730
He's only nice to me because of you.

176
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:08,610
What I said doesn't matter.

177
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:11,220
What matters is,

178
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:12,980
what kind of son he sees you as.

179
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,610
So from now on, study harder,

180
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,180
and never let your guard down.

181
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:20,650
Yes, sir.

182
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:31,980
Who is it?

183
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:33,370
Sir,

184
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:34,130
it's me,

185
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:34,850
Zhuang Shan.

186
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,130
The Marquis has asked for you.

187
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:39,770
Understood.

188
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:08,220
He's inside.

189
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,180
This way, sir.

190
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:36,650
My Lord.

191
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,980
Whenever I'm troubled,

192
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:41,940
I come here to sit for a while.

193
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:44,490
This place

194
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,700
helps clear my mind,

195
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,010
lets me think things through.

196
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,700
I'd be honored to share your burden.

197
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:55,610
Do you believe

198
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,250
General Fu Zhisong's death

199
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:00,300
was truly an accident?

200
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,370
I have no idea.

201
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:16,700
Loyal dogs are often killed

202
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:20,980
when the chase ends.

203
00:13:22,390 --> 00:13:24,010
No matter how great your deeds,

204
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:26,060
they can never outweigh

205
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,250
the heartlessness of an emperor.

206
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,100
But I believe

207
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,650
you're not like General Fu.

208
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,530
He was the late Empress Dowager's nephew,

209
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:40,100
a royal in-law.

210
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:44,100
But you led the charge that took Dongxia's gate

211
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:45,850
and secured a legendary victory.

212
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,130
Surely His Majesty remembers your merit.

213
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,460
With Fu Zhisong dead,

214
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:57,250
the post of Commander of Zhongzhou Forces is now vacant.

215
00:13:59,240 --> 00:13:59,940
In court,

216
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:03,700
no one is more qualified than me.

217
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:07,890
Many officials have already recommended me to the Emperor.

218
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:09,980
So tell me,

219
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:12,850
should I fight for it?

220
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,340
Many current generals

221
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,460
once served under your command.

222
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:19,940
Even your former deputy

223
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:22,370
now leads the Muji Camp outside the Capital.

224
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,700
If you fight for the position now,

225
00:14:26,510 --> 00:14:27,610
I'm afraid the Emperor won't be able

226
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:29,850
to hide his growing unease about you.

227
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:33,180
So I should just sit by

228
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,850
and let the title go to someone else?

229
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:38,940
My Lord,

230
00:14:39,790 --> 00:14:40,490
this matter

231
00:14:40,870 --> 00:14:42,220
isn't just a contest with others.

232
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,370
It's a contest with the Emperor himself.

233
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,580
I believe His Majesty

234
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:49,340
already has his plan in mind.

235
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,250
So perhaps it's best to wait a few days

236
00:14:55,910 --> 00:14:57,530
and see who he ultimately chooses.

237
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,580
And in my opinion, not fighting for it

238
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:01,890
might actually work in your favor.

239
00:15:02,270 --> 00:15:03,730
If you truly wish to command again,

240
00:15:04,670 --> 00:15:06,180
there may be another way.

241
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,420
I want you to do something for me.

242
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:16,850
Please give your order, My Lord.

243
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:19,340
Once you hear this,

244
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,340
there will be no turning back.

245
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:22,580
Think it through.

246
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:27,010
I would die a thousand deaths for your cause.

247
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:35,700
In all my years,

248
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:38,420
I've only lost one battle.

249
00:15:39,550 --> 00:15:40,370
And the one who beat me

250
00:15:41,630 --> 00:15:42,530
wasn't a man,

251
00:15:43,030 --> 00:15:44,460
but a thing called the Gui Seal.

252
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:47,180
The Gui Seal?

253
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,610
In the 35th year of Wuhe,

254
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,730
the late Emperor led a massive campaign against Dongxia.

255
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:57,300
I served as the vanguard then.

256
00:15:57,910 --> 00:15:59,820
We stormed city after city,

257
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,770
nearly conquering the entire land.

258
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,460
But just as we were about

259
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,820
to take the capital,

260
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,610
something strange happened.

261
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:15,490
Go report to the General.

262
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:16,850
Yes, sir!

263
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,090
Are those even human?

264
00:17:20,110 --> 00:17:20,770
Prepare to fight!

265
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,090
Kill them!

266
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:34,860
- Kill! - Kill!

267
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:16,530
The Queen of Dongxia

268
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:17,980
summoned a sacred relic,

269
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:19,290
the Gui Seal.

270
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:22,490
It unleashed an army of ghost soldiers.

271
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:24,810
They're monsters that could not be killed.

272
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:27,490
No matter how strong our forces,

273
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:30,140
they were helpless before them.

274
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,330
Retreat!

275
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:46,900
From that day on, I swore I would find the Gui Seal!

276
00:18:49,550 --> 00:18:53,010
Six years later, the Great Yong regrouped its troops

277
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:56,620
and launched another campaign.

278
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,250
I marched out, ready to die if I must.

279
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:02,380
But this time,

280
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,860
Dongxia had lost the protection of the Gui Seal,

281
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:09,180
and was swiftly crushed into submission.

282
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,420
Yet even after stationing Dongxia

283
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,180
for three years,

284
00:19:18,350 --> 00:19:19,980
I still couldn't find that cursed artifact.

285
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:24,770
A geomancer found this bronze fish.

286
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,050
He discovered the Gui Seal in Dongxia

287
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:29,900
and tried to keep it for himself.

288
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:34,180
I attempted to take it from him, but failed.

289
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:36,420
And I suspect this bronze fish

290
00:19:36,830 --> 00:19:39,460
is somehow linked to the Gui Seal.

291
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:41,700
Perhaps

292
00:19:43,070 --> 00:19:44,010
they're parts of a whole.

293
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:49,980
So the Gui Seal is still on him?

294
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,140
No.

295
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:57,090
Not on him.

296
00:19:57,960 --> 00:19:59,050
He's already dead.

297
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:04,490
That was his fate.

298
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:06,980
He dared to take what belongs to you.

299
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:09,980
He must die.

300
00:20:14,070 --> 00:20:14,980
It's been ten years.

301
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:19,420
I searched everywhere,

302
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:21,900
but still couldn't find it.

303
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:24,980
I'd nearly lost hope.

304
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:27,530
But now that you're here,

305
00:20:28,270 --> 00:20:29,250
it's different.

306
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,010
My Lord,

307
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,940
you want me to help you find the Gui Seal?

308
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:36,700
That's right.

309
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:40,620
My Lord,

310
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,900
I'll do whatever it takes for you.

311
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:45,810
Then this task

312
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:48,330
is yours now.

313
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:51,900
Yes, My Lord.

314
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:57,420
May I ask,

315
00:20:58,270 --> 00:20:59,090
is there only one

316
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:00,940
of these bronze fish?

317
00:21:04,510 --> 00:21:05,180
What do you mean?

318
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:07,380
When I was young,

319
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,940
I studied geomancy under my master.

320
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,420
I learned a bit about Dongxia culture.

321
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,380
Dongxia's early days relied on fishing and hunting,

322
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,940
so the fish became their totem.

323
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:19,700
I've never seen this bronze fish before,

324
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,770
but I've seen many

325
00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:23,290
of their fish symbols.

326
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:27,530
In their paintings, fish always appear in groups.

327
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,290
They're symbols of abundance and prosperity.

328
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:32,940
That's why I asked.

329
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:37,330
Impressive, sharp mind and keen insight.

330
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:38,730
You're right.

331
00:21:39,550 --> 00:21:40,860
This isn't the only bronze fish.

332
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:42,770
I knew it.

333
00:21:43,550 --> 00:21:46,220
You really are the perfect man for the job.

334
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:49,250
Then should I search

335
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:51,250
for the other bronze fish as well?

336
00:21:52,030 --> 00:21:53,810
No need to worry about the others.

337
00:21:54,350 --> 00:21:55,250
I know where they are.

338
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:56,770
Just remember,

339
00:21:58,070 --> 00:21:59,290
once you find the Gui Seal,

340
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,980
I'll make sure you're well rewarded.

341
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:06,250
I'll brave fire and death

342
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,700
to fulfill your wish.

343
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:14,620
The Gui Seal?

344
00:22:16,790 --> 00:22:17,980
I've heard a few tales about it

345
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,660
that have been passed down in Dongxia.

346
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,140
They called it a gift from the Lady of Kunlun,

347
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:24,460
the sacred treasure of their kings.

348
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:27,180
But it always sounded so far-fetched.

349
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:30,810
I thought it only existed in myths.

350
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,490
No one in the Great Yong even knew it was real.

351
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:35,730
Yet your father actually found it

352
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:36,980
and brought it back.

353
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:38,330
I never thought

354
00:22:38,830 --> 00:22:40,730
I'd help the Marquis search for it.

355
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:48,900
Do you still remember the bronze fish

356
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:50,050
in the Marquis's secret chamber?

357
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,900
Last night, I took the chance

358
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,250
to ask about the other two.

359
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,140
He said he knows exactly where they are.

360
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:58,010
Looks like I was right.

361
00:22:58,590 --> 00:23:00,180
They're with the other two enemies.

362
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,900
But even with all the trust he's shown me,

363
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:07,770
the Marquis still refuses

364
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:09,810
to tell me anything about the third person.

365
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:15,490
One step at a time.

366
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:18,530
We've already taken a big step forward.

367
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:20,700
At least you now have the Marquis's approval.

368
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,330
From now on, whatever we do,

369
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,900
we no longer need to hide.

370
00:23:30,030 --> 00:23:30,810
Master.

371
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:33,770
Do you think the Gui Seal really exists?

372
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,620
I don't know either.

373
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:44,250
But there's one thing I'm sure of.

374
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,420
Your enemies

375
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:48,490
never stop searching for it.

376
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,250
So if we find the Gui Seal and the bronze fish,

377
00:23:52,110 --> 00:23:53,180
we'll definitely uncover

378
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:54,140
the third person.

379
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:02,140
My Lord.

380
00:24:02,270 --> 00:24:02,810
My Lady.

381
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:03,530
Zang Hai,

382
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:04,420
have a seat.

383
00:24:05,270 --> 00:24:05,810
Sit!

384
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:11,940
Is there something

385
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,180
to celebrate today, My Lord?

386
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:14,290
You know,

387
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:15,660
the other day,

388
00:24:16,270 --> 00:24:17,530
the Emperor summoned all military officials

389
00:24:18,270 --> 00:24:18,940
to the palace for a meeting.

390
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,090
I claimed illness and didn't go.

391
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:25,770
But the Emperor named Wuma Fu commander of Zhongzhou.

392
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,660
Those who fought

393
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,530
over that position

394
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,050
were demoted or punished.

395
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:34,980
Even though I didn't show up,

396
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:37,050
His Majesty didn't blame me.

397
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,460
In fact, out of concern for my health,

398
00:24:39,790 --> 00:24:40,900
he rewarded me with a thousand taels of silver.

399
00:24:42,310 --> 00:24:43,050
Brilliant move, My Lord.

400
00:24:43,510 --> 00:24:44,420
You didn't fight or scheme,

401
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:45,660
yet won the Emperor's favor.

402
00:24:47,790 --> 00:24:48,660
There's one more thing.

403
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:51,530
A while back,

404
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,770
I submitted a memorial to the Cabinet

405
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:55,330
to recommend you.

406
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:57,380
Zang Hai,

407
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:59,250
your geomantic skills

408
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:00,980
are famous across the Capital.

409
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,940
The Emperor granted you a great honor.

410
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:05,420
Starting today,

411
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:09,140
you are the Imperial Astronomer.

412
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,490
Congratulations, Zang Hai!

413
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:15,180
No,

414
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:16,220
Mr. Zang.

415
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:20,490
Thank you, My Lord.

416
00:25:21,030 --> 00:25:21,900
And thank you, Young Master.

417
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:23,180
Have a seat.

418
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:27,770
The Astronomical Bureau works closely with the Ministry of Works.

419
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:29,620
You and Zhifu

420
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:31,860
will have many chances to work together.

421
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:34,180
Both of you serve under the Emperor's grace,

422
00:25:34,790 --> 00:25:36,770
so make sure to do your duties well.

423
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:39,290
I'll take good care of Zang Hai.

424
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:42,980
Thank you, Young Master.

425
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:46,860
In just six months, Zang Hai rose from aide

426
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:48,530
to a fifth-rank official.

427
00:25:49,110 --> 00:25:50,490
Chu Huaiming was never as skilled.

428
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,010
How could he compare to Mr. Zang?

429
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:55,050
It's all thanks

430
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,420
to My Lord's support.

431
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:57,940
As a fifth-rank official,

432
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:00,380
you'll now have your own residence.

433
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:03,420
Chu Huaiming's old place was unlucky.

434
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:04,700
So I picked a new one

435
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:06,250
for you.

436
00:26:06,790 --> 00:26:07,620
Pack your things.

437
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:09,290
You can move in tomorrow.

438
00:26:11,830 --> 00:26:13,900
I will never forget this great kindness.

439
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,050
No matter where I go,

440
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:17,730
I'll always remember

441
00:26:18,030 --> 00:26:19,980
I came from the Marquis's Mansion.

442
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,090
That's enough.

443
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:23,490
In front of me,

444
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,090
you're no longer a lowly one,

445
00:26:26,270 --> 00:26:27,330
but a proper official now.

446
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,330
Yes, My Lord.

447
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:43,060
[Small Efforts, Lasting Impact]

448
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:46,920
[Zang Residence]

449
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:47,490
Greetings, My Lord.

450
00:27:08,110 --> 00:27:10,180
Father, you're an official too.

451
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:12,050
Why don't you ride in one of those carriages?

452
00:27:12,750 --> 00:27:13,940
Officials ride in carriages,

453
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,900
but walking on foot is still being an official.

454
00:27:16,590 --> 00:27:19,490
Besides, once you get used to riding,

455
00:27:20,270 --> 00:27:21,180
you get lazy to walk.

456
00:27:22,030 --> 00:27:23,090
You may never come down again.

457
00:27:44,380 --> 00:27:48,780
[Zang Residence]

458
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:56,660
[Imperial Astronomical Bureau]

459
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:10,550
[Imperial Astronomical Bureau]

460
00:28:10,550 --> 00:28:11,290
Greetings, Mr. Zang!

461
00:28:11,510 --> 00:28:12,140
This way, please.

462
00:28:31,180 --> 00:28:35,140
[Hall of Affairs]

463
00:28:40,450 --> 00:28:45,100
♪Conceal the ambition in my eyes♪

464
00:28:47,450 --> 00:28:52,990
♪In my palm, I hold a dangerous desire♪

465
00:28:54,460 --> 00:28:56,940
♪Turbulent waves hidden in my sleeves♪

466
00:28:58,010 --> 00:29:00,470
♪Silent thunder echoes around...♪

467
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:02,180
Father, I've grown taller again!

468
00:29:03,110 --> 00:29:03,770
I can now reach the tip

469
00:29:03,790 --> 00:29:04,860
of the armillary sphere!

470
00:29:05,590 --> 00:29:06,490
You've played with it for a while,

471
00:29:07,110 --> 00:29:08,900
but do you know what it's used for?

472
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:10,460
It's for star-gazing.

473
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:14,770
Then do you know how it works?

474
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:16,570
I have no idea.

475
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:17,940
Want to learn?

476
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:18,660
Yes!

477
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:19,900
Come here.

478
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,380
See these four rotating rings?

479
00:29:24,270 --> 00:29:25,050
Try turning them.

480
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,620
Slower...

481
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,860
A bit more...

482
00:29:30,750 --> 00:29:31,250
That's it.

483
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,290
Now move the sighting bar on top,

484
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:34,810
and adjust it by three notches.

485
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:36,420
At night,

486
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:37,810
look through this tiny hole,

487
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:39,180
and you'll see

488
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:40,810
the brightest star in the sky.

489
00:29:41,310 --> 00:29:41,850
Really?

490
00:29:41,850 --> 00:29:46,300
♪My heart burns bright♪

491
00:29:50,020 --> 00:29:53,470
♪I control the shifting clouds♪

492
00:29:53,470 --> 00:29:56,320
♪I command the falling rain♪

493
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,740
♪The compass of the human soul is unpredictable♪

494
00:29:58,740 --> 00:30:03,870
♪There will always be ups and downs♪

495
00:30:04,140 --> 00:30:07,640
♪I stay sharp♪

496
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:10,450
♪I get mad♪

497
00:30:10,450 --> 00:30:13,820
♪When faith burns like the scorching sun♪

498
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:17,440
♪I will sing aloud with you♪

499
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:20,800
♪I am the sowing season♪

500
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:24,460
♪I am the autumn harvest♪

501
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:26,810
[Hall of Affairs]

502
00:30:26,810 --> 00:30:31,070
♪I am the people♪

503
00:30:31,590 --> 00:30:35,720
♪And you are also me♪

504
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:41,530
Greetings, My Lord!

505
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:43,570
Everyone, please rise.

506
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:45,700
My Lord,

507
00:30:46,550 --> 00:30:49,140
I'm Min Shining, Calendar Manager

508
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:50,380
from the Astronomical Division.

509
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:54,290
I'm Lin Wei, Water Clock Manager

510
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:55,010
from the Timekeeping Division.

511
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,460
I'm Shang Jiu, Forest Official

512
00:30:58,510 --> 00:30:59,090
from the Forestry Division.

513
00:30:59,550 --> 00:31:00,050
My Lord,

514
00:31:00,350 --> 00:31:03,420
I'm Chang Wuyi, Manager of Calendrical Calculations

515
00:31:03,510 --> 00:31:04,420
from the Geomancy Division.

516
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:07,860
What about the Mortuary Division?

517
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,250
My Lord,

518
00:31:09,750 --> 00:31:12,050
overseer Shi Quan from the Mortuary Division

519
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,530
said he had urgent matters

520
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:16,330
and couldn't come to greet you.

521
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:18,460
It's all right.

522
00:31:19,830 --> 00:31:20,730
Lord Astronomer,

523
00:31:21,350 --> 00:31:22,980
we've waited a long time for you!

524
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:28,530
The Bureau was founded

525
00:31:29,270 --> 00:31:32,050
to serve the heavens and the people.

526
00:31:33,030 --> 00:31:34,220
Though it's a small department,

527
00:31:34,510 --> 00:31:36,380
whether it's star-gazing, divination,

528
00:31:36,830 --> 00:31:37,940
or geomantic construction,

529
00:31:38,310 --> 00:31:40,220
each craft takes years to master.

530
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:41,420
All of you

531
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:42,770
have been here

532
00:31:43,030 --> 00:31:44,180
far longer than I have.

533
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,180
I'll be relying on you all

534
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,140
for many things ahead.

535
00:31:48,310 --> 00:31:48,860
My Lord,

536
00:31:49,110 --> 00:31:50,090
you're far too modest.

537
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:51,810
If you say that,

538
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:54,180
what does that make the rest of us?

539
00:31:55,790 --> 00:31:56,330
My Lord,

540
00:31:56,590 --> 00:31:57,660
I've always wondered

541
00:31:57,790 --> 00:31:59,250
how did you achieve

542
00:31:59,270 --> 00:32:02,090
such a high rank at your young age.

543
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:05,140
Seeing you today, I'm convinced.

544
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:06,420
Next to you,

545
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:09,980
I'm all flaws and no worth.

546
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:14,530
I hope you won't mind my foolishness,

547
00:32:14,790 --> 00:32:16,010
and will continue to guide me,

548
00:32:16,350 --> 00:32:19,050
so I don't embarrass myself.

549
00:32:20,110 --> 00:32:21,010
Enough small talk.

550
00:32:21,590 --> 00:32:22,570
Let's get to official matters.

551
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:27,140
Have you brought the documents from each division?

552
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:28,330
- We have. - Yes, they're here.

553
00:32:30,310 --> 00:32:31,730
Then let's begin with the Astronomical Division.

554
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:35,490
My Lord,

555
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,330
the Astronomical Division's duties

556
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:39,460
include daily star observations

557
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:40,700
[Astronomical Division Report]
and monitoring celestial phenomena.

558
00:32:40,830 --> 00:32:42,490
We also revise the summer calendar

559
00:32:42,790 --> 00:32:44,530
and precisely mark each solar term,

560
00:32:44,790 --> 00:32:47,940
[Astronomical Division Report]
so the people can follow the seasons and live in harmony.

561
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:53,010
The Timekeeping Division

562
00:32:53,070 --> 00:32:55,660
manages the water clock and reports hours.

563
00:32:55,860 --> 00:32:56,550
[Timekeeping Division Report]

564
00:32:56,550 --> 00:32:58,700
It may seem minor, but precision is crucial.

